HEADWORD: ocher mutation
<hw>o"cher mu"tation</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A humorous variation on
the term <er>amber mutation</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Microbiology, Molecular
biology)</fld> <def>A mutation in which the base sequence of one of the
codons in the messenger RNA has been converted to UAA. Such a mutation
may be conditionally suppressed, as can an <er>amber mutation</er>, by
the presence of a special transfer RNA.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>ocher
mutant</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ochreous</ent>⟦br⟧
